page.title: 06ADULTS DIARY TEBAY JUNE 22
page.content: Woke up 06.30.Going to York with Tebay Women's Institute on our annual outing.The coach was to leave at 09.30 After breakfast and seeing my family off to their Gran's I arrived in time for the coach.The sun was shining but the journey was rather long & by the time we arrived (1230) we were all ready for lunch. After an enjoyable meal we went to Jorvik Viking Centre. waited 20 minutes before our turn.We 'travelled back in time' a 1000 years. A lot of specimens and the whole village had been unearthed under York. Took a taxi to York Minster(Â£1.20) but we couldn't visit the South Tower due to a recent fire.There were tourists mainly Americans and Germans. Everywhere musicians and Morris Dancers entertained the crowds. {Mrs Anne Lowis
